<fr:p>(2) The condition that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> is unital is really critical. For example, we can turn any additive group <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> into a nonunital ring by defining multiplication <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\star  y=0]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  R]]></fr:tex>. There is no maximal ideal for such a ring</fr:p>
